    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is offset by the strength of the output comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96 across all 11 specimens and all three QoIs) and by the direct relevance of the ASTM F1717 protocol to the COU. Overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under static compression-bending loading.",
